Parents and guardians of students enrolled in the Forest City CSD:

Yesterday, we sent an email with an overview of our district's Return To Learn plans (potential instruction/learning models given the COVID-19 pandemic). There is also a survey request.

Please check your email and complete the short survey as that information will help us plan in the coming weeks. The start of the school year is August 17.

If you are a currently-enrolled family and not receiving messages, we need to fix that! It's important, especially given these circumstances, that you are in the loop. Please email kheidemann@forestcity.k12.ia.us.

One thing you can check is if you have downloaded the SchoolMessenger app, go to the menu in the app and Preferences. Ensure your message preferences are set to receive emails- especially general, emergency and weather.

Thank you!

The Families First Coronavirus Response Act allows states to issue Food Assistance benefits to households with children in grades PK-12 who temporarily lost access to free or reduced-price school meals due to pandemic-related school closures. Any child who was enrolled this past school year AND received free or reduced-price school meals as of March 16 is eligible. The amount provided is $307.80 per eligible child.

Visit the Iowa Department of Education's web site for more information. https://www.educateiowa.gov/article/2020/07/07/dhs-announces-pandemic-food-assistance-distribution-plan?utm_source=July+9%2C+2020&utm_campaign=SUMMER+%40+DMPS+Update&utm_medium=email

post_text:
Sharing this information from WCDA for our Worth County families...

Due to the coronavirus, the WCDA will be implementing safety measures for our K-12 Gift Card program. The program will start Monday, August 3 thru Friday, August 28. Card pick up hours are 8:30-4:00, Monday thru Friday. The following guidelines will be strictly adhered to:
No infants, toddlers or children will be allowed in the office. Please make arrangements prior to picking up your cards. There will be no exceptions.
Masks will be required for any person coming into the office.
Only one parent will be allowed into the office at a time.
Social distancing outside of the office is required.
If you have any COVID symptoms, please send a signed statement saying who can pick your cards up for you. Make sure they send their receipts with you.
We are happy to be able to provide parents with our gift cards, but want everyone to remain safe. Thank you in advance for your help.
Deb Hanson/WCDA

Forest City Education Foundation
May 12 at 11:54 AM ·

As you are aware, The Forest City Education Foundation is unable to hold Senior Awards Night in our typical environment due to COVID-19; however, we have developed an alternate format to distribute this years' well-deserved awards to the Class of 2020!

On Wednesday, May 13th, at 6:00 p.m. we will release the link to a pre-recorded video/presentation. The link will be posted on our Facebook page and on our website https://www.forestcityeducationfoundation.org/. The link will also be emailed to the senior class.

A big heartfelt thank you goes out to our family of donors for making Senior Awards Night possible! And although we will not be together, it is our hope that you will watch the video/presentation and know that you are truly making a difference. We couldn't do this without you!

If you've thought about being a substitute teacher, Central Rivers AEA will be offering an online course!

The course will meet via Zoom May 11-15 from 9 a.m to noon each day. The textbook and materials will be provided digitally.

Course description: This 20-hour course is designed to meet the requirements for the Substitute Authorization Program. Receiving a Substitute Authorization will allow an individual who holds a baccalaureate degree to substitute in grades PK-12 for no more than five consecutive days in one job assignment. An individual who holds a paraeducator certificate and completes this course will be authorized to substitute ONLY in the special education classroom (any level) in which the individual is employed, for no more than five consecutive days. The course includes components on ethics, diversity, instructional strategies, and behavior management.

To register, go to this link and create an account. Then search for course # 3405

https://sso.aealearningonline.org/idp/profile/SAML2/Redirect/SSO?execution=e1s1

We are excited to announce our new Forest City CSD app! Search for Forest City CSD in your app store. This free app is available to anyone (no username/password required). It offers 24/7/365 access (one-click icons) to the daily calendar of events, lunch menus, a staff directory, news, school-related apps/programs and more. You can select an event and add it to your own calendar on your mobile device! We will send announcements (push notifications to the app) like news and weather-related messages to the general community through this new app.

Important note: If you have children enrolled in the school district, you will also need the SchoolMessenger (blue icon) app that we've been promoting all summer (see the picture explaining the differences between the two apps).

post_text: So cool Forest City YMCA!
shared_text:
Forest City YMCA
April 5, 2019 at 8:33 AM ·

HAMMER TIME! Not a bad day at work. In our first day of building we have 3 walls framed out and the floor built and decked.

The kids were introduced to many useful things today:
1) Different types of screws and drivers
2) How to read the marks on a tape measure
3) How to read basic building plans
4) Different types of lumber: 2x4, 2x2, 1x4, OSB, structural, treated, pine vs cedar, and so on
5) How to lay out walls and floors
6) What "on center" means
7) What the different settings on a cordless drill are used for and when to use them
8) Where & how to shoot screws: location, toenail and straight driving screws
9) How to square a wall or floor by measuring diagonals
10) LOTS of practice shooting 3" and 2" screws.
11) How teamwork is important in construction.

I would say it was a great day!

I would say it was a great day!

Congratulations To all of the students who auditioned for Allstate today at Hampton Dumont high school!

Special shout out to:
Sarah H., Dan H., Josie E., Anna W., Elijah W., and Emma S. For being selected for the Iowa all-state chorus!

Another special shout out to Micaiah K. for being recalled For the Iowa all-state chorus!

Lastly, congrats to Jasmine S. For being named the first alternate on the clarinet for the all-state band!

We are so proud of all of the students who auditioned today, and can’t thank them enough for their hard work and dedication!

post_text:
7th grade math students are making a difference! Students are baking about 500 cookies today and after school they and FCMS Student Council members will sell cookies along with hot cocoa (donated by Cabin Coffee) at the middle school football games. All proceeds benefit the American Cancer Society.

Students prepped for this service project with Mrs. Ziesmer by working on the recipe (fractions), discussing gross and net profit, reading receipts and by shopping for the best deals on the cookie-making supplies. Thanks to special guests Mr. Lovick, who talked to the kids about cancer, and to Mrs. Pruisner for helping to bake and for sharing information about how she uses math in her candy-making business.

It's a perfect day for some hot cocoa and a delicious cookie or two! See you after school!
